title: Cloudchord - Birdbath and Beyond
description: "Imprint”, the first full length offering from guitarist/producer Derek VanScoten produced under his alias Cloudchord, drops March 21st on Gravitas Recordings. Drawing from obvious jazz and funk roots, the 12 track LP invites subtle influences of future bass, tropical house, and disco to mingle fluidly. However, it’s quickly discernible upon first listen that these influences have cemented into something new; the album is delivered as agreeably familiar yet blissfully fresh, mixing straight beat and broken rhythms with live guitar and poignant synth melodies throughout. Fans of live electronic and indie music will feel at home during the flavorful collaborations with SunSquabi of All Good Records and Los Angeles based trumpet player Erinn Bone.

title: Hurricanes (Wild Love)
description:
Fred V & Grafix haven’t wasted any time, just eight months after the release of their sophomore album the pair are back with a brand new single, ‘Hurricanes(Wild Love)’. The two south-west talents combine their singer/songwriter skills and touch for imaginative production, spearheading a new wave of indie-electro inspired drum & bass.

Fred V & Grafix fully embrace their love for warped beats, warm synths and emotive indie ballads with ‘Hurricanes(Wild Love)’ taking on tight clicky drums, glittered high hats, gentle electric guitar and textured vocal harmonies lead by Fred V himself.

Their ability to create unforgettable,feel-good moments on huge festival stages and sold-out solo tours has kept devoted fans at their mercy. In 2016 alone Fred V & Grafix took to the stage at Glastonbury, Reading and Leeds BBC Radio 1 Dance stage, Let It Roll, as well as touring the USA, Australia, New Zealand and Europe.

There’s been nothing short of support on the airwaves for these two. BBC Radio 1’s MistaJam, Friction, Phil Taggart and Pete Tong all spinning album two tracks and that’s sure to continue as they finish up their third album –more info to come on this very soon, hold tight!

title: Tom Ferry | By My Side (feat. Michaela Baranov)
description:
Straight Summer Tune by https://soundcloud.com/tomferryuk <3 

Repost Submissions // artistsunlimited.com/lesolmusique/submit
Premiere Submissions // artistsunlimited.com/lesolmusique/premiere

UK producer Tom Ferry is gearing up for this spring with this release "By My Side ft. Michaela Baranov". This new dance banger brings the two artists together for the first time and it delivers perfectly. The multi-talented producer Ferry is already well known in the EDM world with previous releases on Armada Music, Ultra and Universal. Tom Ferry is no stranger to being in the spotlight. Tom achieved chart success when his Plateau single was picked up by Ultra Music, collaborating with Duane Harden the track got a to pline and was re-released as Better With You, breaching the top 40 on Beatport’s Deep House Top 100.

Being on X-Factor in 2015 in Australia, Michaela Baranov finished in the top 10 of the popular show. She is currently touring worldwide with Flight Facilities.

With this brand new release on Higher Reign Music, the young Liverpudlian is sure to make a big impression this spring.

title: The Wave (feat. Madcon)
description:
I can't think of a song that makes me feel more like summer than this one. It all started with the beat with a sick old school swing and vibe. I sent it to my friends Madcon and they just killed it. Those guys seriously bring the best energy to their music, and the vibe of their verses is just perfect. We got a old school feeling vocal hook and it all came together! It's getting colder now but this song for me is the memories of my summer and I'm so excited to share it with you. 

From my debut album HAKUNA MATOMA! It's out now and always updating so please subscribe and follow me on this journey! More songs will be added every few weeks and I have A LOT of surprises left :)

When I was in LA we met up and I had this beat idea that had such a good groove and I really wanted to work on with them, so we got together and magic happened! Those guys are incredible, their vibe was good for the beat and they brought that tropical flavor to the track. I hope you like it!

title: Feeling Right (Everything Is Nice) [feat. Popcaan & Wale]
description:
Give it a "Heart" on hypem.com http://awe.sm/gOXXw

Support this track now on:
Spotify: http://smarturl.it/S_MEverythingIsNice
iTunes: http://smarturl.it/MEverythingisNice 
Apple Music: http://smarturl.it/AM_MEverythingisNice
Google Play: http://smarturl.it/GP_MEverythingisNice 

My inspiration for this single is a mixture between old school rhythms combined with a chill tropical flavor. When I created the track I wanted to bring Jamaican vibes together with rap vibes and ended up doing a collaboration together with Popcaan & Wale. I am really proud of this track because I have created something original and inspirational and I hope you like it. This song is all about meeting challenges in life but if you are surrounded with good energy from your love ones "everything is nice". My energy comes from you guys and this track is for my fans and supporters <3 <3

title: Knives
description:
This one is just so special. I heard of these LA guys called FRENSHIP and they write such beautiful songs from the heart so we did a collaboration on this song. I'm all about the good vibes so a lot of my music is really happy and party but I think this gets in the heart a little deeper. It's still so uplifting but honestly the emotion in this song is so incredible, I hope you feel it.

title: Christopher & Matoma - Take Me Back
description: A few month back when I went on my Scandinavian tour I meet this amazing guy called Christopher and together we have made the track "take me back" together. We only had one day in the studio together but when music, having fun, joy and inspiration hit two persons at the same time this is the result and I hope you guys like it as much we did making it. Summer is here with warm weather, sun and people and this track suits the tropical atmosphere perfectly. Enjoy guys❤️☺️

title: EDM (Every Death Matters)
description:
‪#‎EveryDeathMatters‬ - Spread awareness

Please Like, Comment, Repost. 

Support My Music: https://evokehop.bandcamp.com/track/every-death-matters

iTunes, Spotify & Tidal: COMING SOON

On November 12th, 2015 a young woman walked off the deck of a cruise ship during a festival hosted by Diplo's label: Mad Decent. An astonishing lack of media coverage surfaced from the reporters who were actually on board, to the extent that rumors of a media embargo began to spread. The most accepted explanation for her death was drug use leading to inadvertent suicide. In a few months, the story wasn't catchy anymore, and publications shifted back to their regularly scheduled programing about twitter debates and award nominations.
The EDM scene has a problem. It's one that we don't like to admit, because any attempt to quantify the rave scene as different from other music scenes is scary to people who have spent decades trying to legitimize electronic music as an art form, but if we don't admit our problems, we will never be able to work toward solutions. Ultimately, we have to confront the fact that a huge portion of people at festivals are not there for the music; they're there for the unregulated and easily available drugs. I'm not speaking as an outsider here; the rave scene is one that I spent 4 full years fully immersed in, and I've spent 7 years of my own life trying to explain to people that electronic music IS real music.
I attended my first festival when I was 15, and was high for almost every one I attended throughout my raving years. Getting pills at these events is almost comically easy, and I never once heard of anybody I knew getting caught at a show with drugs. At the level of security, festivals don't care if their patrons are using illegal substances, because it's a big part of the draw. At a government level, the war on drugs has been proven to be almost totally ineffective at preventing addiction, use, and deaths like these. The result is an abundance of varied, unmonitored, and dangerous drugs that are sold openly in the rave scene, in a way that I have not seen in any other music culture.
My own drug addiction was developed through my involvement. I took ecstasy at event after event, with no knowledge of the content of the pills, and I wasn't the youngest person I knew doing so. I had friends as young as 13 who were being fed unknown substances in the company of thousands, with virtually no fear of consequence for the people responsible. Dealing drugs at raves is easy. It is profitable, has very rare repercussions for the dealers, but it can be deadly to the users. The most notable publications that claim to cover EDM almost never draw attention to this problem. It's as if we've accepted that people will die, because the idea of trying to solve the problem is too scary, and parties are too fun.
Don't misunderstand me; I don't mean to condemn EDM entirely–far from it. I've spent almost my whole life raised by this scene, and it has defined me. I simply mean to call attention to the potential that the rave scene has to be completely hollow, and turn a blind eye to our very real drug problem. Musicians in the scene do not address these issues. Publications are even less likely to do so. Festivals are making no public effort to tighten security or prevent these deaths. I hate the idea that this weekend, a pre-teen may take several pills with no clue as to exactly what's in them: pills that walked right by the alleged security checkpoints and were openly sold by a man who had nothing to fear. Something needs to change.
Every death matters.

title: Dancing Pineapple Artist Showcase Series: Gamper & Dadoni
description:
Download: www.gamperdadoni.com/downloads

We wanted to close out 2016 with an artist who truly embodies the feel good house movement. Gamper & Dadoni were one of the very first artists we found when Dancing Pineapple began. Remixes of La Roux, Diddy, & Red Hot Chili Peppers put them in the spotlight while their hit singles including Close To You & Far From Home have verified their place in the feel good movement. With some of the most infectious mixes out there, it only seemed fitting to host them on the Artist Showcase Series. 30 minutes of PURE feel good music by some of the best in the field.

[The Artist Showcase Series features mixes composed entirely of the artist's own tracks. A true showcase of talent.]

Tracklist: http://bit.ly/GamperDadoniTracklist

Artist Bio:
 "Isaac Cotec, aka Subaqueous, started making electronic based music in the summer of 2005 working with a project called Psyche Sonics. As of March 12th 2011 the unique character and sound of Subaqueous was born. The music has incorporated beat science to create progressive mid tempo and dance music. Using melodic techniques and musical theory to add layers to the experience."

Forthcoming Album Info:
"“Slipstream” is the forthcoming album from Subaqueous, a new foray into sound from the bass producer Isaac Cotec. “Slipstream” explores the deepest valleys of the soul and takes listeners on a psychedelic bass journey into landscapes of the unknown."

title: Gramatik - Native Son Prequel feat. Leo Napier (MYRNE Remix)
description:
DL: smarturl.it/PrequelRemixes

Thissongissick.com for the premiere: http://thissongissick.com/post/premiere-gramatik-native-son-prequel-myrne-remix

----------------------------------------------

yo,

In a bizarre twist of events, from listening to @Gramatik's Expedition 44 & Street Bangers series as a high school freshman (which really set the groundwork for my approach to funk-infused electronica), to having him personally reach out for a remix was surreal. I had the entire Epigram record to choose from, and my ears were out for this one because of the soulful, tongue-in-cheek vocal. I kept most of the swing from the original record, while giving it a overpowered, gospel-esque boost. Play this one loud!!

love,

M

title: Can't Hold Me Down (ft. Tash Neal of The London Souls)
description:
Pre-Order my new album, Good Will Prevail:  iTunes - http://geni.us/GWPitunes

Politics, the news, senseless deaths... got me feelin' pretty helpless recently. I wrote Can't Hold Me Down as a piece of motivation for those who are feelin' down and struggling in their lives. 

I saw a live performance video of Tash Neal (from The London Souls) playing and knew instantly we had to work together. I wrote the demo and sent it his way. What I got back was magic. Tash is perfect on this tune. 

Don't curse the darkness, be a light. Be the force that pushes others to keep their heads high and stay inspired. Stand up for what you believe in at all costs. Never give up on people.

title: Frank Walker - Run With The Real Feat. DAVS (Original Mix)
description:
Run With The Real.

Hot off of the success of his most recent single, ‘Toes’, Frank Walker is back with another massive summer release.  Frank’s latest release, ‘Run With The Real’, features the amazing vocals of LA-based artist DAVS.  With this latest single, Walker is taking a departure from his traditional house style, experimenting with down-tempo vibes, and crafting a new frontier for his sound. 

‘Run with The Real’ is a grouping of sensual and uplifting melodies that will be hitting the dance floor at the peak of summer.  DAVS has delivered a masterful vocal performance, mixing her sweet vocal performance with edgy lyrics that are sure to turn heads. After listening to such an intoxicating combination, all can agree that with Walker’s powerful production, alongside the amazing vocals of DAVS, ‘Run with The Real’ is guaranteed to be a summer hit.

title: GAMPER & DADONI - Close To You (feat. Daniel Ahearn)
description:
DOWNLOAD / STREAM
https://fanlink.to/closetoyou

HEY GUYS!
So grateful we found Daniel Ahearn, a Singer based in Los Angeles, who wrote this song together with Rich Jacques. We discovered this track on Youtube and really loved everything about it. The lyrics are very intense and emotional. But (and this was most important for us) absolutely authentic. 

We took the vocals and built a whole new arrangement and instrumentation around them. We think this song is brilliant for thoughtful moments, but also while just chilling with your friends enjoying good music!

Please support us by sharing this track with your friends and/or put it into your playlists. But most of all, enjoy it! :)

G&D

Lyrics:
There’s a gentleness I’ve known,
Knew it best when it was fading,
Trying to find my way back home,
Don’t you know, there’s no escaping.

Because I wanted to be loved,
I just wanted to get close to you,
Because I wanted to be loved,
I lost everything I knew.

Turned away from all my dreams,
broken down disintegrating,
Ignored the signs of all deceit,
couldn’t believe - can you blame me?

Because I wanted to be loved,
I just wanted to get close to you,
Because I wanted to be loved,
I lost everything I knew.

Didn’t see until it all was done,
Felt so right to hold someone,
what i saw in you was almost true,
brutal what the heart will do…

Because I wanted to be loved,
I just wanted to get close to you,
Because I wanted to be loved,
I lost everything I knew.

title: Au5 feat Q'AILA - Hit Rewind
description:
Hit Rewind is a relaxed but engaging departure from the dub-centric opener. Glistening, bubble like synths start the tune, and then it settles into a bouncing, intricate drum shuffle that drives a bright, addictive melody. All the layers and textures are all pulled together by a syncopated, buttery-smooth bass line, which expertly compliments Q‘Aila’s unapologetically sultry, soulful vocal lines.

title: Au5 feat Q'AILA - Any Longer
description:
Au5 opens up with “Any Longer,” an earthy, atmospheric bass track that sees his production chops shine through. The song creates a foundation of delicate piano melodies and propulsive percussive rhythms, all while creating a healthy dose of explosive dubstep during the drops. Au5’s production wizardry combines soft and subtle elements along with banging growly bass, the 2 worlds combine perfectly creating a lush pallet for Q’Aila’s smoky, provocative verses and energetic, soaring choruses.

Lyrics:

There’s a man in a cave,
Pale as moon and enslaved
to guard over his wealth
he’s deranged, ill of health
Hunched under the hangings
of pictures and paintings grotesque.
Gripped blind
Only sees what is palpable
Wry is the feast that’s untouchable
Blinded by hunger she pressed
girlish lips to a grape.
Uno, dos, t-t-t-t-t-t-tres
Is the beast really the man
Without a choice in his humanity?
No sight of his insanity?
Tread the rope to grow divine
I’ll never dare step out of line.
Uno, dos, t-t-t-t-t-t-tres
There’s a man in a house
Between drones and his spouse
Snatching up fairytales
And delaying its trails
Stiff under the weight of his duties
and pressed for more time.
Firsthand
He controls all that he can command
Cogging life so it runs as he planned
Terrified by the ticking away of his heart.
Is the beast really the man
without a choice in his humanity?
No sight of his insanity?
Tread the rope to grow divine
I’ll never dare step out of line.
To obey for the sake of obeying…
Well that can only be done by people like you.
To obey, just like that,
No remorse, capitan.
Is the beast really the man
Without a choice in his humanity?
No sight of his insanity?
Tread the rope to grow divine
I’ll never dare step out of line.

description:

Follow Impossible Records:
Beatport: bit.ly/ImpRecsBP
Soundcloud: bit.ly/ImpRecsSC
Facebook: bit.ly/ImpRecsFB
Twitter/Instagram: @impossiblerecs
www.youtube.com/channel/UCUL7mjOZzzuSIXS4nMrIHvw

Impossible Records welcomes ‘Phenom’ to the family with his debut EP, ‘Red Giant Strikes’. ’Red Giant Strikes’ is heavy, melodic and sometimes a bit humorous setting the tone for the rest of the album. ‘Phenomenon’ and ’Lethal Dose’ are the perfect example as what classifies him as strong sound designer who has a great sense of melody. ‘Biking is my Drug’ is a track inspired by an ironic representation surrounding racism that features chart topping MC, ‘Lloyd Lawrence’. ‘Recoil’, a track about strained and difficult relationships, is a collaboration with the Ukrainian alt-rock band ‘Karl of Most’. The future is definitely bright for this talented producer as he gently pulls you into his world, luring you in like a Siren in the night with his dubstep serenade.

brought to you by Night Owl Collective and PlayItLouder, we are proud to present to you a truly one-of-a-kind emotional future R&B tune by Eli Way and singer/songwriter Rachel Marie; two up and coming musicians that have joined forces to create a song that will be remembered for years to come, and we are so honored to be able to release it.

this track is something so powerful and touching, and really sets a beautiful mood with a deep vibe that will send chills through your body. we cannot wait to hear more collaborations between Eli and Rachel! there will definitely be more to come and we believe they will be an unstoppable team.

be sure to follow both of them and check out more of their music, and also, HUGE shout out to Stereogum for premiering the song!

title: The Hex
description:
"The Hex" tells a story about the uncertainty of the future, specifically our future as a band. We came up with the name on our very first tour when we found a book about sacred geometry. All spiritual meanings aside, this track tells the story of our very first national tour from running out of gas on the side of the highway to rocking sold out shows. As we woke up everyday, we had no idea what that day had in store for us and we were living life by the moment. We truly discovered that life is about the journey, not the destination. Feeding off energy gained from the road, "The Hex" is a summary of 22,000 miles of driving across the US in a Jeep Grand Cherokee. 

Written, Composed, Mixed by Arja Adair, Luke Sims 
Mastering by Chris Cox

title: Au5 - Return To Moonland
description:
Moonland is representative of an eternal place. The infinitely cyclic nature of the moon reflects the flow of emotion and the dynamic of the life cycle. 

Return to Moonland is about revisiting a familiar place once lost or forgotten, perhaps where we came from. Upon the return, a new perspective is realized. We leave home, have new experiences, and through that process gain a new appreciation and understanding of ourselves, our origin, and our destiny.

title: G-Eazy - Me Myself & I (HYTYD Remix)
description:
So so much to love about the Summer. Weather, festivals, clothes, general vibes, and of course the soul that makes all that go ’round: the music. Summer tunes are so fittingly warm and airy, and there’s few people out there that do them as well as HYTYD. His remix of James Bay’s “Let it Go” more than impressed us with its tasteful simplicity and grounded emotions, this time he’s in our spotlight thanks to a beach ready remix of G-Eazy’s radio hit, “Me Myself & I.” Beachside, poolside, in the car, in your room, in the office…I don’t care where you listen to it, this is bound to get you moving. Once again, his instrumental arrangement is clean and concise, and his vocal edits are sublime. While tropical house tends to bludgeon you over the head with the idea that it’s meant for the Summer, HYTYD’s light and lofty style implies it with the utmost maturity, leaving you to imagine it in any setting; we’re hoping to hear this baby all season long, and you make it a reality with the free download below. Enjoy.
- @EDMTUNES

title: SAG, MountBlaq & HYRO - That Sound [DDD047]
description:
FREE DOWNLOAD: http://dirtydut.ch/DDD047-DL

Listen on YouTube: http://dirtydut.ch/DDD047-YT
Listen on Spotify: http://dirtydut.ch/DDD047-SP

Next up on Dirty Dutch Digital, collaboration fuels the fires of uncompromising, bass-driven electronic music. SAG, MountBlaq & HYRO join forces for an utterly intoxicating, relentless and totally fierce house cut that holds nothing back and summons every ounce of energy to blast off into overdrive.
Highly rhythmical, restless and ferocious in attitude, “That Sound” kicks off with snapping drum machines, shattering synths and driving sub-bass. The ghetto vocals are the call to arms that initiate the process of spilling over into a frenzied, tough attack that charges forward in a wall of floor-shaking bass, distorted synths and brutal beats. Spine-tingling melodies swoop in and create a lighter, more airy aesthetic before the track once again kicks on into its wild and frenetic attack of the central nervous system. “That Sound” is both the venom and the antidote. Use it wisely.

Stream it here: http://bit.ly/StreamSkeletonDance

Apashe continues down a path of bringing high-quality bass to the table alongside his already extensive hybrid catalog. "Skeleton Dance" sees the Montreal producer collaborating with fellow Canadian LENA on a wicked record that will even get the dead on their feet and rocking. Fit with a ritualistic sounding vocal, rich horns, and Apashe's signature basses, "Skeleton Dance" is a spiritual call to all those who love to rage, both living and departed.

Enjoy & Survive!

description:
FREE DOWNLOAD: bit.ly/shighfree
BANDCAMP: bit.ly/fhighbcamp
iTUNES: bit.ly/fhighitunes
BEATPORT: bit.ly/fhighbpt
SPOTIFY: bit.ly/fhighspfy
---------------------------------

Westwood is proud to welcome SugarBeats to the Westwood Recordings family with their debut full-length offering, the “Fly High” LP. 

The Oregon-based duo has been bringing the funk up and down the west coast for over 5 years now, playing major festivals such as Lightning in a Bottle, What The Festival, and Burning Man. Garnering steady support from the Future Funk community and most recently winning 1st place in our Shambhala Remix Competition for the legendary producer Opiuo, we've had our eyes on the duo ever since as they've been building momentum towards their much anticipated debut album, "Fly High." The album features all original compositions recorded over the past year with a diverse cast of talented musicians and vocalists. Inspired by the sounds of funk, hip-hop, glitch, and future bass, SugarBeats have truly managed to uncover a sound of their own.

title: Mr. Bill & Freddy Todd - Colloidal Drip
description:
Buy the album here - http://mrbillstunes.com/product/settling-for-mediocrity/

The title of the album is based on a feeling I believe all artists experience. Whenever I'm working on music (or anything for that matter) I'm always trying to chase an idea I have in my head and present it in reality where it can be observed, quantified and appreciated, only to realise that my idea or vision is too extreme or disproportionate to my skill set, leaving me constantly in a state of abandoning my art at a point where it can be classed as 'complete I guess' and settle for mediocrity.

TLDR: Art is never finished, only abandoned. We all settle for mediocrity.

title: Mennska - Love Postponed
description:
Let us know what you think and click the [↻ Repost] button if you like the track.
Buy on iTunes:  https://goo.gl/2nIHCs
________________________________________
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
Here's a mellow tropical/melodic house original chronicling the abrupt ending of a relationship where the protagonist of the story is left clueless as to why his girl left him.

In a usual Mennska fashion we showcase our love for the juxtaposition of that lighthearted summery vibe coupled with melancholic lyrics.
________________________________________
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
- Lyrics -

Verse 1:
Used to be, that you were down with me
But time changes everything
it used to be, you were a part of me,
but time changes everyone

I don’t know what I’ve done to deserve this
I thought that you were mine
I confess I did not see it coming
You never gave me a sign

Chorus:
Too late, to make you mine (is it)
too late, am I out of time? (is it)
too late, am I on my own? (is it)
too late, cause love postponed?

Too late to call you up (is it)
too late, have you had enough? (is it)
too late, to change your tone? (is it)
too late, cause love postponed?

Verse 2:
Used to be, that you were in love with me
but now, these days you walk on different plays
it used to be, that you would cry for me
but now your tears are dry as there’s some other guy

I broke like glass, my senses are numb
can’t get my head around what you’ve become
But I still want you!

Chorus:
Too late, to make you mine (is it)
too late, am I out of time? (is it)
too late, am I on my own? (is it)
too late, cause love postponed?

Too late to call you up (is it)
too late, have you had enough? (is it)
too late, to change your tone? (is it)
too late, cause love postponed?

Outro:
T - Double O - L - A - T - E (repeatedly)

title: NEST HQ MiniMix: Shawn Wasabi
description:
Spending hours, days, months, etc., crafting a collage of samples into a cohesive piece of new music is awesome art, and one Shawn Wasabi (@sssshawnnnn) is quickly becoming a master at. Aside from creating new melodic themes from found fragments of hundreds of different songs, he also performs and records each work live. You may have seen one of Shawn’s many multi-million breaking Youtube videos, but not many know these are each performed in one take. The kid’s a legend, and he’s one of the first to be pushing a cute, bubbly and hyper sound to a bigger audience in the states. We’re stoked to be sharing Shawn’s NEST HQ MiniMix with y’all today.

title: Havok Roth - Mothership
description:
Premiered by @NESTHQ
http://nesthq.com/premiere-havok-roth-mothership

First track of 2016! Free download. Thank you for your continuous support!

"Miami-based producer Havok Roth has returned guns blazing in 2016 with a new release for each month of the year. You may recognize the artist from his pre-hiatus remix of Jay Cosmic’s “Supercell” and his VIP Edit Pack. His sound is a combination of main stage EDM and reckless hard bass music, but his first tune for this year, “Mothership”, is an absolute headbanger that plays more to the grittier side of things. Apocalyptic horns and Far East arpeggios pair with an over-encompassing mechanical sound design and alienesque accents for a truly massive tune." -NEST HQ

title: Whatcha Gonna Do (The Funk Hunters Remix)
description:
"Whatcha Gonna Do (The Funk Hunters Remix)"
by Fort Knox Five ft. Mustafa Akbar
FKX088 - Fort Knox Recordings
http://www.fortknoxfive.com

Buy it here:
https://fortknox.bandcamp.com/album/whatcha-gonna-do-ft-mustafa-akbar
http://www.junodownload.com/products/fort-knox-five-mustafa-whatcha-gonna-do/2950296-02/
https://pro.beatport.com/release/whatcha-gonna-do/1644999
https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/whatcha-gonna-do-ep/id1056560465


Tracklisting:
1. Whatcha Gonna Do (The Funk Hunters Remix)
2. Whatcha Gonna Do (Father Funk Remix)
3. Whatcha Gonna Do (Original Mix)
4. Whatcha Gonna Do (The Funk Hunters Remix Instrumental)
5. Whatcha Gonna Do (Father Funk Remix Instrumental)
6. Whatcha Gonna Do (Instrumental Mix)

Fort Knox Five is proud to present their latest single, “Whatcha Gonna Do” featuring Mustafa Akbar with killer remixes by The Funk Hunters and Father Funk.  

Fort Knox Five’s longtime friends and brothers in funk, Vancouver-based The Funk Hunters have delivered one of the baddest floor-rocking remixes ever!  This track debuted in the Fractal Forest at the 2015 Shambhala Music Festival where it electrified the masses and brought the crowd to a fever pitch. The Funk Hunters have injected their signature sound into “Whatcha Gonna Do” with big drops, huge hooks, and enough glitch and disco to make you put your hands up!  This is a guaranteed banger full of West Coast synths and chunked out beats. Easy to see why this one is already a staple of The Funk Hunters amazing live sets.

The next “Whatcha Gonna Do” Remix is by Father Funk, the Leeds, UK based producer known for his clever remixes and smashing edits.  Father Funk’s remix begins with Rob Myers’ retro wah-wah guitar and Mustafa Akbar’s soulful party chants then quickly escalates into a wobbly, bass heavy, butt-shaking glitch-hop monster! Hold on tight as Father Funk breaks it down, takes it back to the original soul vibe and then finishes strong with a deep groove.

The original mix of “Whatcha Gonna Do” featuring Mustafa Akbar is a quintessential Fort Knox Five slice of retro disco funk – straight from the ’70s – infused with tight, electronic production. With its live horns, funky guitar riffs and Mustafa Akbar’s soulful hooks, Fort Knox Five has created an irresistible party anthem. DJs and radio stations alike have rallied behind “Whatcha Gonna Do”, making it one of the lead tracks from Fort Knox Five’s 2015 album Pressurize The Cabin.

title: 03. ChrisB. - Space Dust [OUT NOW!!!]
description:
An electro-organic tidal wave of harmony and divergent sound design illustrates the beginning of Headtron all-star ChrisB's new EP "Triangular Objects", out on Gravitas Recordings January 15th. It's been nearly two years since his last solo release, but Los Angeles native Chris Brown reveals that this time has been spent hard at work. These six individual gems, ranging from the main room to the bedroom, are sure to stand apart in any bass music lover's collection.

A barrage of psychotropic and integral melody distinguishes both "Fluid Dynamics" and "Space Dust", with large detuned leads bringing grit to what might otherwise be whimsical tunes. "Trendy" shows Chris' interpretation of the recent trap movement - but instead of reproducing the same exhausted sound palette, this intrepid producer merges his unique synthesis construction with heavy 808s to create an entirely fresh offering. Meticulous percussion steers the intro of the title track, soon giving way to reserved jazz keys set atop a laser-infused bassline. The EP comes to a close with the upbeat "Eye in the Sky", which boasts complex synth work and funky bass riffs suitable for a 5-string Fender.

title: I Dropped It (Halfred & Enzalla Remix)
description:
The Great Mystery Remixes Part 2 ::: https://desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/the-great-mystery-remixes-part-2 

Earlier this year Desert Dwellers released their most diverse album in the duo's long career. The Great Mystery was the first full length collaborative project just between the main founders Amani Friend and Treavor Moontribe, and featured a wide range of styles and aesthetics from downtempo and psychedelic dub to tribal trance to exotic house and techno flavors.

To celebrate the special release, Desert Dwellers have curated an ambitious two-part remix album with a total of 25 contributions from some of the brightest luminaries and rising talents across the underground electronic music landscape. The Great Mystery Remixes Part 2 is slated for a November 1st release on the DD Bandcamp page, and features sonic reinterpretations from Emancipator, Aligning Minds, Mumukshu, Sixis, David Starfire, Whitebear, Erothyme, Mystral, Master Minded, Halfred & Enzalla, Lulacruza, Bumble, Soohan, and Supersyllius. With artists from across the globe and musical genres, these carefully crafting renditions of Desert Dwellers' The Great Mystery are a potent combination of immersive soundscapes that pay a loving tribute to the original compositions.

The Great Mystery Remixes Part 2 ::: https://desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/the-great-mystery-remixes-part-2

title: The Great Mystery (Tribone Re-Stomp)
description:
https://desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/the-great-mystery-remixes-part-1

Earlier this year Desert Dwellers released their most diverse album in the duo's long career. The Great Mystery was the first full length collaborative project between the main founders Amani Friend and Treavor Moontribe, and featured a wide range of styles and aesthetics from downtempo and psychedelic dub to tribal trance to exotic house and techno flavors.

To celebrate the special release, Desert Dwellers have curated an ambitious two-part remix album full of contributions from some of the brightest luminaries and rising talents across the underground electronic music landscape. The Great Mystery Remixes Part 1 is slated for a September 21st release, and features sonic reinterpretations from Gaudi, Liquid Stranger, Hibernation, An-ten-nae, Kaminanda, AtYya, Tribone, Twin Shape, Land Switcher, Drumspyder, and Govinda. The second part will be released in late October with contributions from Emancipator, Whitebear, Sixis, Mystral, Supersillyus, Halfred, Master Minded, and many others. With artists from across the globe and musical genres, these carefully crafting renditions of Desert Dwellers' The Great Mystery are a potent combination of immersive soundscapes that pay a loving tribute to the original compositions.

title: Rising, Rising
description:
Cat"a*clasm\ N. A breaking asunder; a violent disruption.

Buy on iTunes: bit.ly/CataclasmiTunes
Watch the mini documentary: bit.ly/MakingOfCataclasm
Photography by Dustin Hollywood

And I Can See Your Blood Flow.

I'm not sure when it started, but for a long time now I've had this reoccurring daydream where I walk outside my house, look upwards, and start to slowly float towards the sky. Suspended in the air, rising up, the people and buildings on the ground getting smaller and smaller... It has always given me this very unique feeling that I can't pin down; Almost like a nostalgia for something that hasn't happened yet. It's poetic. Profound. My pulse quickens, I get this invigorating feeling of moving on to another world. It's almost a sort of "L'appel Du Vide." Suddenly nothing else matters. I close my eyes and feel absolute peace.

Where am I going? What am I escaping? What awaits me?

I'm not sure where this single came from inside of me, but I know it has to do with that image. The entire time I was writing, recording and producing this, I felt it. It doesn't have specified verses and choruses, it floats from movement to movement, slowly evolving and growing. I wanted it to be a journey. Every time I listen to it, even now, I feel I'm getting a glimpse into that other world. The clouds are parting, I'm venturing into the void. I hope that, in some small way, it can make you feel the same way.

title: Desert Dwellers - View Of Lanaikea - AN - TEN - NAE Remix
description:
Available through Bandcamp: https://desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/the-great-mystery-remixes-part-1

Read the review from @theuntz: www.theuntz.com/news/liquid-stran…stery-remixes-v1/

"Earlier this year Desert Dwellers released their most diverse album in the duo's long career. The Great Mystery was the first full length collaborative project between the main founders Amani Friend and Treavor Moontribe, and featured a wide range of styles and aesthetics from downtempo and psychedelic dub to tribal trance to exotic house and techno flavors.

To celebrate the special release, Desert Dwellers have curated an ambitious two-part remix album full of contributions from some of the brightest luminaries and rising talents across the underground electronic music landscape. The Great Mystery Remixes Part 1 is slated for a September 21st release, and features sonic reinterpretations from Gaudi, Liquid Stranger, Hibernation, An-ten-nae, Kaminanda, AtYya, Tribone, Twin Shape, Land Switcher, Drumspyder, and Govinda. The second part will be released in late October with contributions from Emancipator, Whitebear, Sixis, Mystral, Supersillyus, Halfred, Master Minded, and many others. With artists from across the globe and musical genres, these carefully crafting renditions of Desert Dwellers' The Great Mystery are a potent combination of immersive soundscapes that pay a loving tribute to the original compositions.

Available through Bandcamp: desertdwellersmusic.bandcamp.com/album/th…s-part-1

Westwood presents the official winning remixes of the 2015 "Opiuo - Life" remix competition! Co-presented by Canada's acclaimed Shambhala Music Festival, the remix competition garnered hundreds of submissions from producers around the globe, 5 of which were selected by the Judges for official release on Westwood Recordings: Grand Prize winner, Sugarbeats. 1st Runner Up, Toby Emerson. title: CloZee - Revolution
description:
Donate and Download: http://music.gravitasrecordings.com/album/revolution

French producer Chloe Herry, better known by her stage name CloZee, has spent the better part of the last year on tour between North America and Europe. “Revolution”, her latest pay-what-you-want offering on the Gravitas Music imprint, could be seen as a reflection of those journeys. In some moments, the listener may find themselves deep in a lush forest surrounded by towering trees. Just the next minute, the surroundings morph into an underground venue among sweaty bodies all pulsating to the same beat. The true beauty of CloZee’s music can be found in this subdued yet intricate sophistication; the juxtaposition of elegance and detail create subtle contrast which can be seen swirling together upon observation of any of these five songs. 

Her graceful entrance begins with “Anticlimax”, a well named tune that focuses more on the evolving groove and tender melodies than any pronounced drop. The title track cleverly utilizes glitchy percussion to offset the orchestral and middle eastern harmonies. “Sankar’s Lake” gets the body moving with a catchy rhythm and flow, intelligently using bass to keep the pace progressing. Resolving on a haunting tone, “The Path To Heaven” again places focus on the delicate yet impactful drum work, culminating in a perfect conclusion for the album.

title: Whitebear x Tribone - Sensory Overload
description:
Collab with @tribone29

Free of stylistic constraints and immaculately produced, Whitebear’s aptly titled “Liberation”, is a bold statement in artistic freedom and originality. Having drawn inspiration from far and wide across the psychedelic stylistic spectrum, 'Liberation' speaks of a deeply transmutational journey, woven symbolically through intricately spacial sound design and dynamically entrancing grooves. 

Whitebear's third EP is an immense listening experience, taking the individual on a voyage to the very edge of their existence. A journey of self-actualisation, channelled and transmitted through sonic waves of aural ecstasy, each musical offering taking you deeper through the passage of change. With his signature blend of mid-tempo psychedelia, ancestral percussion, and growling vibrations that permeate your soul, Whitebear is about to take you on an intense journey into the very heart of your being. Prepare for the unexpected and almost ineffable experience that is 'Liberation'- this is Whitebear at the cutting edge of auditory evolution.

title: Halfred & TRIBONE - Different Angle - The true-light-of-darkness"(OUT NOW)
description:
J.Jesso: "The True Light Of Darkness is a literary exploration of the turbulent struggles involved in entheogenic shadow-work. focused on the Author's more disturbing encounters with the magic psilocybin mushroom, this book confronts the demons laying wait in the dark recesses of the psyche. This is its soundtrack.Featuring exclusive audio samples from the author, this OST is flows with dark and tripped out midtempo psybass and womp that bends the mind and moves the body. "
This album Launches July 10th along with the book. You can pre-order just the album through the link above, or you can preorder the book via the link below and get a free copy of the soundtrack and access to the exclusive online launch webinar.

www.truelightofdarkness.com

The entire soundtrack  that has been created alongside the book featuring other great psychedelic musicians like Wattsun &Mighty Oak, Icaro, Omwom, Alejo, Psydell will be officially released on 10th July so stay  tuned!!! It will be a great one!!! Tracks included:

1) Alejo -  The substrate
2) Psydell - Audible Visions
3) Omwom -  Bubble up
4) Icaro - True Light
5) Halfred & Tribone - Different Angle
6) Wattsun - Totemic Pulse (Daitya & Wattsun TLOD Edit)
7) MightyOak - Mind Adventures

description:
Hi Everyone,

It's a typical Cotts & Ravine hardcore set, with lots of quick mixing and hands up hardcore. I was really happy with it and I hope you enjoy listening!

Cheers,

Cotts

title: One And Only
description:
Out now :') DJ's get the MP3 here : http://apple.co/1O3zsFU
_____________________________________
Send me <3 on Hype Machine (◡‿◡✿): 
http://hypem.com/track/2c8f2/Sable.+-+One+And+Only

@thatsableguy
www.facebook.com/thatsableguy
Stream on Apple Music : itun.es/au/XKVq8
Stream on Spotify : spoti.fi/1Rn0o8V

"One and Only’ is a love song with a hidden meaning. Its focus is on the relationships people build online and then the feelings of attachment they develop from that. It's a pop song at heart dressed in a club aesthetic" - Sable

When the infectious club bounce of Perth producer Sable’s breakthrough single 'Feels So Good' hit the airwaves over the Summer of 2014, it marked a significant shift in Australian electronic music. Marrying the jersey bounce & club crushing production chops of then break out stars like Ryan Hemsworth & Nadus, with an undeniably Australian polish & sheen. Sable spent the rest of the year on multiple country wide tours, ushering in a new era of Aussie club music that came to include the likes of Basenji & UV Boi, & set the stage for Australian radio's introduction to the hyperactive blissed out pop music of Lido, Cashmere Cat, and more.

Featuring for the first time, the voice of Sable himself, ‘One and Only’ comes filtered through androgynous larynx tones & a GPS dizzying vocal, with the 'Current Location' marker hovering over somewhere not of this earth. He once again fly’s the flag for Splendour this year, showcasing new material from the upcoming EP.  In the words of Sable himself.

title: High Maintenance - A Brand New World
description:
Preorder for the 17th July 2015: http://bit.ly/APORN058_APSHOP
(Available exclusively from Beatport from the 5th July)





Once again demonstrating his high-octane production and unique brand of drum and bass, High Maintenance comes back around to deliver a riveting power liquid ballad.




Let The Light Shine opens with smooth pads that give way to a killer piano line and vocal chops. Relentlessly building up to the conclusion, the tune drops with full force summer vibes.




A Brand New World shows High Maintenance’s darker side while maintaining his signature high-energy sound. Raw filtered reese grooves and ever solidly polished production value make this tune a sure-fire hit as a peak time dance floor killer. 




For all things High Maintenance, keep it locked to AudioPorn Records.

title: Defunk - Forever and Never ft. Marshall McGee [LostinSound.org Premiere]
description:
Download here: 
http://bit.ly/dfunkdfree

@defunk-music

Westwood is proud to present "Delights" - The new album from Canadian electronic producer, Defunk. With a constantly evolving taste for bass music, Delights pushes his sound into new territories as he combines his favorite elements of midtempo, glitch, and future bass music with old school funk, soul, and hiphop. The result is a sexy palette of funky rhythms, dirty drops, jazzy solos, and special guest appearances from featured vocalists and instrumentalists alike including the Ragga Twins, Sam Klass, Marshall McGee, the Raya Brass Band and more. Keep your sights on Defunk this year, as he teams up with Pretty Lights Music artists in Telluride, CO and opens for Big Gigantic and RL Grime at Red Rocks Amphitheater.

title: Illenium - I'll Be Your Reason [NEST052]
description:
“Skrillex founded Nest to shine a light on untapped talent -- and San Francisco native https://soundcloud.com/illeniumofficial fits the bill.” – Billboard

Denver-based producer Illenium (aka Nicholas Miller) has linked up with NEST for the release of his latest single, “I’ll Be Your Reason”, out today, June 8th. Falling somewhere in the vast realm of future bass, the new single sees Miller harness his superlative ability for melodic production, utilizing hazy vocals from Irish songwriter, EDEN, for a moody, downtempo jam.

“I wanted to surprise people with this tune and show that music can both be beautiful, complex, and diverse all at the same time,” Miller explains. Complete with fluid textures and incisive hip hop percussion, Illenium creates a gratifying juxtaposition of floaty atmospherics and assertive, bass-heavy hits that highlights the rising producer’s multifaceted approach to his craft.

title: Dhawa Sunrise: Halfred - Snowons
description:
'Snowons' by Halfred - Sixth track from [OUTTA010] 'Dhawa Sunrise'

@halfr3d
www.facebook.com/halfr3d

[UPDATE] 

This album was originally organized with the idea to build a science lab at Shree Prabhat Higher Secondary School in Dhawa, Gorkha, Nepal. Unfortunately the 7.9 magnitude earthquake shook Nepal the day after release, destroying most of Dhawa, including the school. The country needs billions in funds to recover from this tragic event and in our small way, we are redirecting our efforts through this project to create a fund for rebuilding Dhawa. PLEASE consider donating to our cause in exchange for a cutting-edge music compilation and help us restore normality to a highly vulnerable community. 

Many thanks 

---------------------- 

Original Project Idea: 

‘Dhawa Sunrise’ is an exclusive compilation based around the themes of future-thinking and/or ethnic inspired texture-heavy music. The aim of the album will be to fund equipment for and create a Science Lab at the Shree Prabhat Higher Secondary School in Dhawa, Gorkha, Nepal.

For more details, watch video in buy link.

Album release date: 24.04.15

title: Sugarpunch - I Wonder / Scenic Route [EP Minimix]
description:
● Available to buy here: Beatport » http://btprt.dj/1Ovl6OX, Bandcamp » http://bit.ly/1a8iOWw, iTunes » http://apple.co/1NC7ynZ, Addictech » http://bit.ly/1E7V1xp, Spotify » http://bit.ly/1WCWDun

● Glitch Hop Community is glad to provide a platform for Sugarpunch to release their debut EP. The group consists of two Hungarian producers, Mongoose & Ivan Beres and a vocalist Wyllywyll (US).
Their first EP ‘I Wonder / Scenic Route’ includes 2 original tracks and instrumental versions too. The tunes bring forth much fun and positivity, real spring vibes, glitch hop merged with some jazz and a pinch of pop kicked up with hip hop vocals so the carefree fun is guaranteed while listening to this one.
The song ‘I Wonder’ is coming with a music video so be on the look out!
This EP is sweet like sugar but still can hit you like a punch! 

● Tracklist
01 I Wonder
02 Scenic Route

title: Warpboiz ft. Warp 9 (Out Now)
description:
As we achieve warp speed we hit time dilation and the journey turns psychomimetic. When we discussed the direction of this track with our collaborator(the excellent) Warp9 the concept for the ep hadn't evolved beyond a yin and yang idea. Luckily, Adam's music all sounds like it's beamed directly from a far distant world so we weren't surprised when we got the final draft back how well it worked. It fit perfectly into the eternal universe spacetime odyssey final concept. We think of the outro horns on Warpboiz as the warning that the ride is about to get bumpy.

title: Cheshire - Smokey Joe's (Beat Fatigue Remix)
description:
Like the track? Click the [Repost] ↻ button!

SUBSCRIBE: bit.ly/subscribetoadaptedrecords
 
Out March 9th

Follow Cheshire: 
● Youtube: http://youtube.com/user/cheshiretactics
● Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/cheshirenz
● SoundCloud: https://soundcloud.com/cheshire
● Twitter: https://twitter.com/Cheshiremusicnz

Follow Beat Fatigue: 
● Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCh4YxFATEnYPYyhg7z8TAQg
● Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/pages/Beat-Fatigue/603641212989426
● SoundCloud: https://soundcloud.com/beat-fatigue
● Twitter: https://twitter.com/BeatFatigue1

Follow Adapted Records
● Facebook: http://facebook.com/Adaptedrecords
● SoundCloud: http://soundcloud.com/adapted-records
● Twitter: http://twitter.com/adapted_records
● Website: http://adaptedrecords.com
● Youtube: http://goo.gl/p46EN1

Cheshire Music's rise to prominence in 2015 only validates the hype from his "Funk On" and "Simply Lifted" EP's. There's no better tribute to celebrate his library and style than this eclectic 13-track compilation of remixes from his peers.

With a midtempo origin, there was plenty of room to improvise and each artist delivers a unique imprint. FarfetchD shines with one of his grittiest tunes ever, a magnificent rendition of "We'll Be There." Functionality goes awry with the bassy wobbles of Beat Fatigue, Staunch, Orphic, SpekrFreks, and SugarBeats. Accordingly, there is plenty of emerging talent on deck to put a churn in your stomach with face-melting edits from Minoru, Funkanomics, mat tha hat, DJ Wood, Squelch Music, One Hand Clap, and Synergy Sound.

title: No More (Ain't That A Glitch EP)
description:
Beat Fatigue is back again on Adapted with another incredible EP. Ain’t That A Glitch features six original pieces from the dutch mastermind. Staying true to his groovy style, Beat Fatigue is the epitome of Glitch Hop goodness.

Opening it up, the first track, No More, has a driving beat and a soulful vocal to get you ready for the journey ahead. Slashy Cricket sticks more to the electronic glitch side of things and will have you hypnotized. The title track features some face melting guitar and an insanely tasty drop. Walking All Cool is wonderfully pleasing melodically and the instrument choice is nothing short of perfect. Quarterboucer kicks it back to a sexy vibe to chill out to. All That Muting is wonderfully named and Beat Fatigue really capitalizes on his talents with the six string. Always a great choice, this EP will have you endlessly enthused about the power of Glitch.

description:
Like the tracks? Click the [Repost] ↻ button!

Support: ► 
Beatport: http://www.beatport.com/release/one-day-live-your-life-ep/1452846

SUBSCRIBE: bit.ly/subscribetoadaptedrecords

Twitter: https://twitter.com/ThomasVent

Follow Adapted Records: 
Facebook: www.facebook.com/Adaptedrecords 
Youtube: bit.ly/subscribetoadaptedrecords 
Twitter: twitter.com/Adapted_Records 
Beatport: www.beatport.com/label/adapted-records/24915 
SoundCloud: soundcloud.com/adaptedrecords

After an insane release with his EP Modern Bluesman, Thomas Vent is back to sate your craving for bluesy glitch hop!  Always putting tons of soul into his releases, One Day Live Your Life is no exception.  Utilizing instruments like the harmonica, guitar and unbelievable bases, this producer from Poland is always a joy to listen to.

Kicking this EP off with Deep In Your Soul, the track is full of energy and will hit you right in the chest with bass.  New Orleans Style pushes Vent’s normal sound and heads a bit more into the future; complex, melodic and insane production set this track in a world of its own.  The title track gets back to the funk and will propel you to a party unlike anything you’ve ever experienced.  Make sure to grab this EP and join Thomas Vent in One Day Live Your Life.

title: Christina Perri - Burning Gold (Autograf Remix)
description:
Like the track? Click the [↻ Repost] button!

Buy link: http://found.ee/XDdYF

For us, the beauty about the Future is the endless possibilities it holds. In essence, it's a blank canvas waiting to be painted on. We'd love nothing more than to 'build' and 'make' a Future that's all our own. That means doing everything ourselves from scratch, bringing the hand of the artist back. So as we've been building a studio in the backyard and working on our live show, we wanted to start this new "Future Nites" series of remixes and originals with an eye on creating music for these live performances. We added a marimba to the live set, and can't wait to get some more analog gear into the studio so we can take these Future Beats to the next level.

It's been a fun ride for us putting all our heart and soul into this new project, so we hope this song takes you on an equally epic journey. As summer turns to fall, and day turns to night, we hope that you'll paint these empty canvases of endless possibilities with us. You do it by sharing and blasting music out into the world, with every action you make. It's about leaving your mark on the world. It's about leaving your Autograf. This is Future Nites.

title: MVTH - Metal Jacket
description:
A full metal jacket (or FMJ) is a bullet consisting of a soft core (usually made of lead) encased in a shell of harder metal, such as gilding metal, cupronickel or less commonly a steel alloy. This shell can extend around all of the bullet (alternatively termed a total metal jacket round) or, more often, just around the front and sides with the rear lead part left exposed. The jacket allows for higher muzzle velocities than bare lead without depositing significant amounts of metal in the bore.

title: Singularity - Lael Bellotti, Dave Cortex, Melanie Synn, Harnois
description:
singularity
noun

    1. the state, fact, quality, or condition of being singular
        "he believed in the singularity of all cultures"

    2. PHYSICS | MATHEMATICS
        a point at which a function takes an infinite value, especially in space-time when matter is infinitely dense, as at the center of a black hole.

--- Four years ago, four aspiring musicians from four corners of America's east coast found themselves each at a crossroads, with a desire to go against the grain. After a chance meeting, a bold experiment was undertaken: to create a functional environment dedicated to nurturing creativity and production. Pursuing parallel endeavors, but helping each other along the way, the four joined forces. Singularity is the culmination of their paths becoming one. ---

    The Party:

    DC industry veteran Dave Cortex (INSOMNIFIED, Hotfingers, Funkedge) has DJ'd in the nation's capital and beyond for 15 years now. Wearing many hats over his career, Dave has found success as an event promoter, music journalist, web & media designer, and his most recognizable role: producing a decade's worth of funky, groove-centric, genre-defying house music.

    Virginia native Lael Bellotti (INSOMNIFIED, Neuroscience, Kaywood) holds a degree in mechanical engineering, but set his sights on engineering of a different sort. Becoming the protégé of studio whiz Dave Cortex, he began learning the art of music production. Lael's meticulous attention to detail came in handy in the studio, and it wasn't long before cranking out big room bangers was second nature.

    A rare breed of musician with both vocal quality and pro studio chops, Baltimore-born-and-raised Melanie Synn (INSOMNIFIED, Funkedge, Hotfingers) spent her formative years performing in theater before discovering the DC rave scene. Melanie's expressive and sultry underground sound transcends genres, and her unique ability to create infectious hooks and harmonies with both the vox and DAW is second to none.

    Josh Harnois (INSOMNIFIED, Silk Royal Records, Funkedge) has taken DC by storm with a genre-defying style that fuses electronic music with classical and jazz elements. Bringing together his impressive skills on a variety of live instruments (keyboard, sax, guitar) with serious studio skills, Harnois creates raw, lush, & sexy sounds in a fusion of harmony, melody, and technology.


--- Collectively, their work has been supported by industry heavyweights including David Guetta, Paul Oakenfold, Myon and Shane 54, Dirty Vegas, Tritonal, and Michael Woods; they've remixed Lazy Rich, Magnetie, Hirshee, Max Vangeli, and Swanky Tunes; and performed alongside Kaskade, BT, Josh Wink, DJ Dan, and Nick Warren; to name a few.  Together, this is their Singularity. ---

- BEATPORT EXCLUSIVE: RELEASING OCTOBER 27

▲▲▲▲▲▲▲▲▲▲▲

"It opens with some super funky bass line and a guitar riff that could have been written by Stevie Nicks herself, gradually layering on the synth and vocals in a musically masterful build up. The drop drops you into this galactic colour-pop world that brings the kind of good vibes and whimsical splashes that force you to bounce and groove with the new energetic musical direction. This remix has taken a simple pop tune and made it into something with more spice, it's obvious to see the flare of Elk Road's personality poking through, constructing something with greater instrumental depth and variety." - Stoney Roads

title: Apashe - Golden Empire (ft. Zitaa)
description:
Available now on Beatport: http://bit.ly/GoldenEmpireEP
--

For more music, follow me on Facebook and Twitter:
www.facebook.com/Apashe.Official
www.twitter.com/Apashe_Music
__

Apashe is out to conquer new territories with his new EP, “Golden Empire”. The Belgian producer has brought out his full arsenal of sonic weapons to craft an epic pair of bass-heavy juggernauts that will destroy dancefloors worldwide.

The title track of the EP is a 6-minute bass odyssey that covers an astounding amount of musical ground. The big drums and gritty bass lines that have made Apashe so well-known are of course prominently featured, but they are neatly tucked into endless layers of brass, between filtered guitar strums and airy choir sections.

The oriental-flavored B-side, “Sand Storm”, is no less impressive. Montreal MCs Odalisk throw down a few vicious bars over snake-like synth lines before Apashe brings the heavy bass back in what is sure to be another trapstep hit for the Kannibalen artist.

Enjoy & Survive
tag_list: Apashe "Golden Empire" Zitaa "Sand Storm" EP "Kannibalen Records" "Sound Des" Hybrid 100bpm "Black Gold"

title: DJ Cotts - Hardcore Ch00nage Vol.5 (2006)
description:
Another week another installment of Hardcore Ch00nage! below is a letter I sent out when I posted this promo CD to people back in 2006 including a tracklist. Hope you enjoy!
==========================================
Well guys,

It’s that time again!!!!

Another few months = Another Instalment of Hardcore Ch00nage.

I know I say this every single time but this volume (5) is the best volume to date. I keep surprising myself and im learning constantly new tricks and ways to make the mixes better. 

Thanks again to everyone that is a member and continues to listen in from Ahn.fm. I really love you guys there and it makes doing this fun and worthwhile. Without you guys being there and listening in to our small shows I don’t think I would still be doing it now. 
I guess sending out these cd’s is somewhat of a thankyou for sticking around and showing support for a long time. (This year and a half has gone damn quick).

Anyway this cd is pretty much a Raver Baby compilation. It showcases the new stuff mostly from the raver baby side of things, and I know that will make most of you out there happy to hear that! I have listened to it about 15 times over and im really pleased with how it turned out, so I hope you guys will to. 

Keep an eye on your mailboxes for Hardcore Ch00nage Vol.6 I am most of the way through it already believe it or not, and it should be coming your guy’s way soon.  Also I would always like to hear feedback from you guys and how to make future cd’s even better.

Thanks for everything,

Enjoy the cd.

Cheers,

Cotts.


Tracklisting:

1. Styles and Breeze - NYE Intro
2. Access 3 - Promised Land (Squad-e remix)
3. Euphoria - Playing Games
4. D-Code - My Direction (Squad-e remix)
5. Audiolush - Feel the power (Dougal and Gammer Remix)
6. Hixxy - I have to Dream (Dougal and Gammer Remix)
7. N-Trance - Set You Free (Hixxy Remix)
8. Darren Styles - Save Me
9. ETron - Time of my life (No Left Turn Remix)
10. Darren Styles - Jealous
11. Hixxy and Re-Con - I Can Wait (Squad-e Remix)
12. Reese - Voodoo Magic
13. Heaven 7 - Kontact Dj
14. Stabilised - Drop the Needle (Stormtrooper Remix)
15. Brisk & Ham - Crazy Love (Gammer Remix)
16. The Acolyte Feat. Amy - Draw To You (Original mix)
17. Hixxy & Styles - Happiness
18. Impact - The Voice

title: Cobalt by SanKtum
description:
With the release of his Free EP, Sanktum is establishing himself as a star on the rise. “Cobalt”, which features trancey and ambient dynamics, transforms into an electro blippy and grungy drop. The ability to infuse two different genres creates a harmonious sound that is like no other and shows why he will become a master at his craft.

Purchase it here: http://www.beatport.com/track/cobalt-original-mix/4880285
